eligious beliefs, ideologies of authority and lifestyle in Seljuq times influenced cultural and artistic production, urban and rural architecture, monumental inscriptions and royal titulature, and practices of religion and magic. It also presents today’s challenges and new approaches to preserving the material heritage of this vastly accomplished and influential civilization.ContributorsViola AllegranziDeniz BeyazitPatricia BlessingSheila CanbyRoberta Giunta Margaret GravesCarole HillenbrandRobert HillenbrandRenata HolodLorenz KornStefan MasarovicLeslee Michelsen Andrew PeacockScott RedfordMartina RugiadiYasser TabbaaDeborah TorGeorge SalibaRustam ShukurovAlessandro Sidoti Mario Vitalone  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mrz 2022) 0aArt, SeljukzTurkey. 0aArt, TurkishxHistory. 0aSeljuksxCivilization. 4aIslamic Studies. 7aARCHITECTURE / History / Medieval.2bisacsh1 aAllegranzi, Viola, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeyazit, Deniz, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aBeyazit, Deniz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBlessing, Patricia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCanby, Sheila R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGiunta, Roberta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGraves, Margaret S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHillenbrand, Carole, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHillenbrand, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHolod, Renata, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKorn, Lorenz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMasarovic, Stefan, econtributor.